---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Voidless Tale" description="About the Voidless Tale project.">
  <section class="page-section prose">
    <article class="hero__panel">
      <span class="eyebrow">About the project</span>
      <h1>About Voidless Tale</h1>
      <p>
        This starter keeps the site lean on purpose: a homepage, an about page, and a devlog that
        can be updated through Git-backed content editing. That gives you a strong base for adding
        lore, screenshots, a mailing list, or release notes later.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you want to grow it next, the best follow-ups are usually a media gallery, a proper game
        feature section, and a fuller content model in `public/cms/config.yml`.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
